  "text": "Quantum state redistribution with entanglementassisted classical communication. A fundamental result in quantum information theory is the fact that one qubit can transfer two bits of classical information by consuming an additional singlet, a phenomenon also known as superdense coding [CITATION_1] . On the other hand, two bits of classical communication together with one singlet can be used to teleport one qubit [CITATION_2] , see also [CITATION_3] and references therein.",
